  <span id="freeText8635851213490280355" style="display:none">Not really impressed by this series, if this book is representative. The title character is veeeery aristocratic, and sensitive, and aesthetically refined, to a degree which makes Lord Peter look like a commoner; unfortunately, there is none of the witty amusing dialogue, so the whole story is rather humorless. Much ink is spilled portraying the way the inspector is torn between his upper class code and his code as an officer of the law, much Like in P. D. James series where the inspector is torn between his life as a poet and his life as a la detective, but this is much more angsty, and lacks the elegant prose of James.</span>
