    <a title="Callie Stockman" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7276240-callie-stockman"><img alt="Callie Stockman" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1325377650p2/7276240.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4048525070?book_show_action=true">Jul 02, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Callie Stockman" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Callie Stockman" href="/user/show/7276240-callie-stockman">Callie Stockman</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7276240-callie-stockman?shelf=mystery-suspense-thriller-oh-my">mystery-suspense-thriller-oh-my</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4048525070" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4201158155251095718">I am deep in the hole of UK murder mysteries and I don&apos;t think I ever want to climb out. <br/><br/>George continues the series with a snow-ladden house in Scotland where there&apos;s been....a murder! It&apos;s surely one of the guests and Lynley and Havers are inexplicably called in to handle the case. But why? It&apos;s not their jurisdiction. And more importantly, why is Lady Helen involved?<br/><br/>Particularly interesting in this one is Havers and Lynley&apos;s thoughts on their friendship. It was so mis-matched that I actually </span>
  <span id="freeText4201158155251095718" style="display:none">I am deep in the hole of UK murder mysteries and I don't think I ever want to climb out. <br /><br />George continues the series with a snow-ladden house in Scotland where there's been....a murder! It's surely one of the guests and Lynley and Havers are inexplicably called in to handle the case. But why? It's not their jurisdiction. And more importantly, why is Lady Helen involved?<br /><br />Particularly interesting in this one is Havers and Lynley's thoughts on their friendship. It was so mis-matched that I actually had to double check to make sure I hadn't missed a book in between. Havers believes she owes her career to Lynly and is willing to sacrifice everything for him, while he didn't even want her on the case. <br /><br />Also, Lady Helen and Lynley's relationship is under the microscope and that tension added nicely with overall "whodunit" quality of the book. <br /><br />I am here for keeps!</span>
  <a data-text-id="4201158155251095718" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


